==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Technic
<hw>Tech"nic</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[See <er>Technical</er>,
<pos>a.</pos>]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The method of performance in any
art; technical skill; artistic execution; technique.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>They illustrate the method of nature, not the <qex>technic</qex>
of a manlike Artificer.</q> <rj><qau>Tyndall.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <pluf>pl.</pluf> <def>Technical terms or objects; things
pertaining to the practice of an art or science.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Technical</ent>⟦br⟧
